  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sudan - Emergency Assistance to Mitigate the Impacts of Floods on Schools in Khartoum State</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Heavy rains and floods have hit Sudan hard in the past few years. In August 2009, flooding struck much of Khartoum State, killing 20 and displacing 50,000 others. Some 66 schools were affected, and 10 were severely damaged. In 2012, torrential rains caused similar damage in White Nile and Blue Nile States. The forced closure of schools meant attendance dropped dramatically.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Bank provided emergency grants to help the Sudanese government rebuild and repair schools damaged by the 2009 and 2012 floods. This has benefited tens of thousands of students. The Bank&#x2019;s relief efforts also covered school supplies, such as text books.</narrative>
  </description>
